&lt;h1 id="motivate-the-paper"&gt;Motivate the paper&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A scrupulous writer, in every sentence that he writes, will ask himself at least four questions, thus:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What am I trying to say?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What words will express it?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What image or idiom will make it clearer?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is this image fresh enough to have an effect?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;George Orwell, &amp;ldquo;Politics and the English Language&amp;rdquo;, 1946&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Enjoy your work</title><link>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/orig/enjoy-your-work/</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:52:36 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/orig/enjoy-your-work/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/zh/enjoy-your-work.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
